version_description: This is my best attempt at the basic chord structure of the song, without the main bass riff.

A full transcription of the chords and tabs that go into the album Twin Fantasy (Mirror to Mirror). This is not the Face to Face versions, which I may end up transcribing in the future. All tracks aside from Cute Thing require no capo.

Beautiful song. Listen for the basic strumming pattern. For most of the song, you can just keep your fingers in the standard position for the D chord and alternate the first finger between the second fret of the G string and the second fret of the D string (muting the E and A strings for both the D and Em9 chords). For the last half, basically just vamp on D-to-Em9, and move around the fretboard and shout and wail as the spirit moves you.
